review_blob: Pour clean. Had roasted notes of coffee in the nose. Thin palette which is appropriate for style. Taste was patent wuth a ting of spice.

Aroma had hints of caramel and banana. Deep honey color a vit hazy. Not much in head retention. The palate was not to thin. Taste was clean with hints of caramel and extremly ckean finish overall very balanced ale.
Not much in the nose other than than a sour note. Slight tang and effervescent palate. Taste of fresh peach with a very clean finish. Can see myself shrinking mourn on a hot summer day.
Weak on the nose and paleta still an improvement from the original batch. Worth a try.
beer_name: Cigar City Guava Grove Farmhouse Ale
